<p><strong>Update:</strong> After posting I found a solution:</p>  <pre><code>var cbcf:ClassFactory = new ClassFactory(ComboBoxGridItemEditor); cbcf.properties = { dataProvider: colors }; col.itemEditor = cbcf; </code></pre>  <p>Will add any other details as I work this through.</p>  <hr>  <p>I'm using a Spark <code>dataGrid</code> component and am initializing it through actionscript in order to be able to handle a variable data set.</p>  <p>It works fine but I am having trouble defining inline editors.I am trying to use the provided <code>ComboBoxGridItemEditor</code> but get a type coercion error (below). All of the examples I have checked use <code>mxml</code> to define the dataGrid elements. Is it possible to do what I want through AS3?</p>  <p>Simplified example of what I am trying to do:</p>  <pre><code>var colors:ArrayList = new ArrayList(["red", "blue", "green"]); var colorEditor:ComboBoxGridItemEditor = new ComboBoxGridItemEditor(); colorEditor.dataProvider = colors;  // not relevant code stripped for (i = 0; i &lt; model.editableHeaders.length; i++){     col = new GridColumn();     col.dataField = model.editableHeaders[i];     col.visible = false;     col.editable = true;     col.itemRenderer = colorEditor;     columnHeaders.addItem(col); }  mapData.columns = columnHeaders; </code></pre>  <blockquote>   <p>Implicit coercion of a value of type   spark.components.gridClasses:ComboBoxGridItemEditor to an unrelated   type mx.core:IFactory</p> </blockquote>